This paper investigates the geometric properties of functions learned by ConvNets, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves analyzing the weights of a trained network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses empirical methods to analyze the data, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL).
